column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
Weather/waves: sunny- mild waves.  Readings are very impaired due to excessive weed growth.

Note:  There were 2 samples on this day at this lake.  1 in a bay near a horse farm (high total phosphorus)- and 1 at the Deep Hole site.  The lab phosphorus bottles were apparently switched around- so a correction was made to tag the higher TP reading to the Bay station ID 10030698 - per conversation with Sue Graham who talked to the volunteer and Donna Sefton 10/28/2009. (- Jennifer Filbert)
the sky is very overcast. we had 7" of rain in the last 3 days.
the weather was clear + calm.  the water is very brown. saw a couple blue heron. greg smith is the only one doing the monitoring at this time.
it rained last night. today during the test it was overcast.
today the levey broke on upper spring lake. flooding our lake lower spring.
today it was overcast today is overcast today is overcast
the weed harvester has not been cutting. the milfoil has pretty much died off. this is the best i have seen this lake for this time of year. i have been here for 16 years. today was overcast.
sunny-not a cloud in the sky
sunny when i dropped the disk
sunny today. there is alot of dead vegitation in the lake on the east end.
today is clear-a little breezy today the skies are clear
today is sunny. yesterday i watched 3 deer feeding on the lilly pads
today was overcast. jennifer filbert was with me today
today is cloudy + windy today is cloudy + windy
today at the time of the test was sunny + windy

overcast at the time of the test
today is cloudy-windy. May 8th we had a treatment done for invasive plants
